at <a href="https://philpapers.org/" target="other">PhilPapers</a>, with links to its database.</td>
</tr>

</table>
</blockquote>
</div>

<div id="other-internet-resources">

<h2 id="Oth">Other Internet Resources</h2>

<ul>

<li>Fan, Jie, Davide Grossi, Barteld Kooi, Xingchi Su, and Rineke
Verbrugge, 2020,
 &ldquo;<a href="https://export.arxiv.org/abs/2001.03945" target="other">Commonly Knowingly Whether</a>&rdquo;,
 manuscript.</li>

 <li><a href="http://hintikkasworld.irisa.fr/" target="other">Hintikka&rsquo;s World</a>,
 a graphical, pedagogical tool for learning about epistemic logic,
higher-order reasoning and knowledge dynamics.</li>

 <li><a href="https://github.com/rkirsling/modallogic" target="other">Modal Logic Playground</a>,
 a graphical interface for drawing and evaluating formulas of modal
propositional logic.</li>
</ul>
</div>

